  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6775.25 sitting below the 6784 flip strike in a PIN regime, dealers are currently buying the dip as their long gamma positioning dictates. The massive positive gamma wall at 6800 (42.1B) creates a strong magnet effect, while the recent GEX surge (-22.2% in 1min) suggests heavy options flow is amplifying dealer hedging activity. Expect mean reversion higher toward 6800 with dealers providing liquidity support on any further weakness toward the 6770 negative gamma zone.\n\nKey levels: 6770 (dealer buying accelerates), 6784 (regime flip), and 6800 (heavy dealer selling pressure).\n\n**Bottom line:** expect a bounce back toward 6800 with dealers cushioning the downside.",
